          "type": "text",
          "text": "I need to understand how the AgentLog codebase handles git commit association with traces. \n\nPlease search for and analyze:\n1. The git hook service implementation - likely in packages/backend/src/services/gitHookService.ts or similar\n2. The post-commit hook handling - how it reads traceId and creates spans\n3. The MCP implementation that creates traces and should write to git config\n4. Any code related to AGENTLOG_TRACE_ID environment variable handling\n\nFocus on finding:\n- Where git config \"agentlog.traceId\" is written\n- Where git config \"agentlog.traceId\" is read\n- How spans are created with traceId association on git commit\n\nReturn the file paths and relevant code sections that handle this flow.",
